##E.Python.Install.1:
#Write installation instructions for an operating system of your
choice and add to this documentation.
*For mac users you can install the latest python version, python 3.8 by visiting the python site https://www.python.org/downloads and following the dowload instructions
*Python can also be installed on the mac system by using homebrew and by typing the code "brew install python" into the terminal.
*Python can also be installed using Ubantu by typing the following code:
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt install software-properties-common
    sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa -y
    sudo apt-get install python3.8 python3-dev -y
*Python can also be installed via conda with the following code:
    cd ~
    conda create -n ENV3 python=3.8.1
    conda activate ENV3
    conda install -c anaconda pip
    conda deactivate ENV3
*New versions of python can also be installed busing the following code:
  *If you have an older version of python on your mac computer, you need to deactivate that older version first:
      pyenv deactivate
      pyenv uninstall ENV3
  *Then you can install the newer version of python using the code:
      pyenv install 3.8.1
      pyenv virtualenv 3.8.1 ENV3
      ENV3
      pip install pip -U

