ENV3 in your terminals to switch between python 2 and 3.
*You can install pyenv by using the code:
    pyenv install -l
*You can install python versions 2.7 and 3.8 using the code:
    pyenv update
    pyenv install 2.7.16
    pyenv install 3.8.1
*Associate python with ENV2 and ENV3 commands
    pyenv virtualenv 2.7.16 ENV2
    pyenv virtualenv 3.8.1 ENV3
 *To switch to python version 2.7, use the code: ENV2
 *To switch to python 3.8, use the code: ENV#

##E.Python.Install.3:
#Why do you not want to use generally anaconda for cloud
computing? When is it ok to use anaconda?
*You do not want to use anaconda for cloud computing because it comes with too many packages, many of which you will never use and will take up valuable time and data storage space on your computer
*Anaconda may interfere with default python interpreters and setup
*Anaconda terminology can also be confusing since the version number in python is not related t the anaconda version number.
*For the root directory anaconda does not use the root term for the root user, this can also be confusing.
